1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,500
I was afraid when I arrived

2
00:00:04,209 --> 00:00:09,042
Because we heard about them, that they execute and behead

3
00:00:09,042 --> 00:00:10,542
And other such things

4
00:00:11,334 --> 00:00:13,334
So I was more afraid than usual

5
00:00:16,459 --> 00:00:17,959
They interrogated me

6
00:00:18,626 --> 00:00:21,500
And they said, You will now go inside

7
00:00:22,042 --> 00:00:24,375
And the <i>hajji</i> is the one who knows what he will do to you

8
00:00:25,542 --> 00:00:28,959
So I became more terrified than usual

9
00:00:30,834 --> 00:00:32,334
That is what happened to me

10
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,709
Interviewer: This person who received you

11
00:00:34,709 --> 00:00:36,876
And the other who took your belongings

12
00:00:36,959 --> 00:00:39,834
How did they treat you, was their manner soft?

13
00:00:39,876 --> 00:00:42,459
No, no, their manner was soft

14
00:00:43,792 --> 00:00:46,292
He said, What brought you here

15
00:00:46,876 --> 00:00:50,083
I said, I don’t know, the <i>hajji</i> brought me and I don’t know the reason

16
00:00:50,584 --> 00:00:54,083
And I told you that I had medicine I’d distributed for free to people

17
00:00:55,334 --> 00:00:58,918
Because of medicine, meaning I was going to him because of the medicine

18
00:00:59,792 --> 00:01:01,292
But if there is something other than medicine I don’t know

19
00:01:02,751 --> 00:01:03,751
They took me inside

20
00:01:04,751 --> 00:01:08,209
Interviewer: After you walked from the caravan and entered the interrogation room

21
00:01:08,626 --> 00:01:10,959
The one who took you and led you into the interrogation room

22
00:01:11,042 --> 00:01:15,083
Did he blindfold you when he brought you to the judge or not?

23
00:01:15,125 --> 00:01:18,542
No, they brought me in normally and did not blindfold me

24
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,167
And I knew the judge

25
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:23,167
He was sitting outside drinking tea

26
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:25,209
He had a mole, and his name was Ayoub

27
00:01:26,626 --> 00:01:29,125
Interviewer: Was he from Mosul?
Witness: No, he was from Diyala

28
00:01:29,834 --> 00:01:31,209
From Diyala, and his nom de guerre was Abu Yahya

29
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:33,292
Interviewer: About how old was he?

30
00:01:34,209 --> 00:01:38,042
He was in his forties, about 45, or 43

31
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:40,250
Interviewer: Was he the judge of this court?

32
00:01:40,292 --> 00:01:41,792
Yes, and he was the one who conducted the interrogation

33
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:44,667
Inside the hall
